<materialsCitation id="3B45515BF76CB12DB182FE47361A4293" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3766756399" box="[199,1059,439,466]" collectionCode="VERIFIED" location="Durban" municipality="River" pageId="25" pageNumber="546" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="KwaZulu-Natal" typeStatus="holotype">
<collectionCode id="ED3CC3C3F76CB12DB182FE47331A428D" box="[199,291,440,466]" pageId="25" pageNumber="546">VERIFIED</collectionCode>
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F76CB12DB06FFE403362428D" box="[298,347,447,463]" pageId="25" pageNumber="546">TYPE</typeStatus>
LOCALITY: uMlazi 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BF6C17CF76CB12DB36CFE4830534293" box="[553,618,439,465]" pageId="25" pageNumber="546">River</collectingMunicipality>
mouth, near 
<location id="8EF20DDDF76CB12DB245FE4831624293" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0384EA10F76CB12DB1D2FF6837314054:8EF20DDDF76CB12DB245FE4831624293" box="[768,859,439,465]" municipality="River" name="Durban" pageId="25" pageNumber="546" stateProvince="KwaZulu-Natal">Durban</location>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49E995E4F76CB12DB222FE48361A4293" box="[871,1059,439,465]" country="South Africa" name="KwaZulu-Natal" pageId="25" pageNumber="546">KwaZulu-Natal</collectingRegion>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C337088DF76CB12DB182FE2437314054" pageId="25" pageNumber="546" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B925B06F76CB12DB182FE2437314054" blockId="25.[151,1437,223,790]" pageId="25" pageNumber="546">
COMMENTS: 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F76CB12DB00EFE2333BC42B4" box="[331,389,476,502]" pageId="25" pageNumber="546">Type</typeStatus>
locality upper Umlaas River (= Camperdown, 
<collectingRegion id="49E995E4F76CB12DB2D8FE24366142B4" box="[925,1112,475,502]" country="South Africa" name="KwaZulu-Natal" pageId="25" pageNumber="546">KwaZulu-Natal</collectingRegion>
) according to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F76CB12DB5BAFE2432D04158" author="Gyldenstolpe, N." pageId="25" pageNumber="546" pagination="1 - 116" refId="ref28755" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1926) Types of birds in the Royal Natural History Museum in Stockholm. Arkiv f or Zoologi, 19, 1 - 116." type="journal article" year="1926">Gyldenstolpe (1926)</bibRefCitation>
. However, Wahlberg stayed at the mouth of the uMlazi River from 
<date id="FF937DC6F76CB12DB545FE00368A415B" box="[1024,1203,511,537]" pageId="25" pageNumber="546" value="1841-03-11">11 March 1841</date>
until at least 7 May (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F76CB12DB1DAFDDC3301417C" author="Brinck, P." box="[159,312,547,574]" pageId="25" pageNumber="546" refId="ref28132" refString="Brinck, P. (1955) Swedish exploration of South African animal life during 200 years. In: Hanstrom, B., Brinck, P. &amp; Rudebeck, G. (Eds.), South African Animal Life. Vol. 1. Almquist &amp; Wiksell, Stockholm, pp. 11 - 61." type="book" year="1955">Brinck 1955</bibRefCitation>
). Entries in the journal are intermittent through March and there are only two entries for April. The next entry on 7 May states that he had returned to Congella, Durban. There is no note that Wahlberg had gone to Camperdown during this period, and all specimens collected in March, April and early May are labelled uMlazi River or Durban (the latter probably in error). The 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F76CB12DB2CBFD6F31F841E8" box="[910,961,656,682]" pageId="25" pageNumber="546">type</typeStatus>
locality can be restricted to uMlazi River mouth, near Durban. In his 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F76CB12DB09AFD4B302B418C" box="[479,530,692,718]" pageId="25" pageNumber="546">type</typeStatus>
catalogue, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F76CB12DB3DFFD4C3182418C" author="Gyldenstolpe, N." box="[666,955,691,718]" pageId="25" pageNumber="546" pagination="1 - 116" refId="ref28755" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1926) Types of birds in the Royal Natural History Museum in Stockholm. Arkiv f or Zoologi, 19, 1 - 116." type="journal article" year="1926">Gyldenstolpe (1926: 46)</bibRefCitation>
observed that 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F76CB12DB520FD4C3752418F" author="Sundevall, C. J." box="[1125,1387,691,718]" pageId="25" pageNumber="546" pagination="96 - 111" refId="ref29984" refString="Sundevall, C. J. (1850) Foglar fran sodra Afrika. Ofversigt af Kongliga Vetenskaps-akademiens forhandlingar, 7 (4), 96 - 111." type="journal article" year="1850">Sundevall (1850: 103)</bibRefCitation>
had priority over Cabanis’ paper of the same year and thus that 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F76CB12DB276FD27368941B0" authority="Cabanis, 1851" authorityName="Cabanis" authorityYear="1851" box="[819,1200,727,754]" class="Aves" family="Locustellidae" genus="Catriscus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="546" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="B9598714F76CB12DB276FD27363F41B3" box="[819,1030,727,754]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="546">Catriscus apicalis</emphasis>
Cabanis, 1851
</taxonomicName>
(corrected date, see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F76CB12DB1D2FD0433AA4057" author="Dickinson, E. C. &amp; Overstreet, L. K. &amp; Dowsett, R. J. &amp; Bruce, M. D." box="[151,403,763,790]" pageId="25" pageNumber="546" refId="ref28440" refString="Dickinson, E. C., Overstreet, L. K., Dowsett, R. J. &amp; Bruce, M. D. (2011) Priority! The Dating of Scientific Names in Ornithology: a Directory to the Literature and its Reviewers. Aves Press, Northampton, 319 pp." type="book" year="2011">Dickinson et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
) is a subjective junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F76CB12DB259FD04373D4054" authority="Sundevall, 1850" authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1850" box="[796,1284,763,790]" class="Aves" family="Locustellidae" genus="Bradypterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="546" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brevirostris">
<emphasis id="B9598714F76CB12DB259FD0436024057" box="[796,1083,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="546">Bradypterus brevirostris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F76CB12DB506FD04373D4054" author="Sundevall, C. J." box="[1091,1284,763,790]" pageId="25" pageNumber="546" pagination="96 - 111" refId="ref29984" refString="Sundevall, C. J. (1850) Foglar fran sodra Afrika. Ofversigt af Kongliga Vetenskaps-akademiens forhandlingar, 7 (4), 96 - 111." type="journal article" year="1850">Sundevall, 1850</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
